<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="062" project="smart-todo-decoupling-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Loop prevention: `sprk_synchash` + thread-local skip-flag + per-field last-write-wins</title>
    <phase>Phase 7: Graph Sync Engine</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4-6 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>061</dependencies>
    <blocks>066</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, api, backend, integration-test</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Cross-cutting sync correctness concern; affects handler + webhook + plugin. FULL rigor with integration tests.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>P7-W3</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Builds on 061; modifies same handler + adds threading concerns.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Implement three-layer loop prevention per FR-23: (a) `sprk_synchash` — 16-hex truncated SHA-256 of canonical JSON of synced fields; computed before every outbound write; compared on inbound notification to drop echoes. (b) Thread-local "skip outbound" flag — set during inbound writes so the resulting Dataverse update doesn't re-enqueue an outbound message. (c) Per-field last-write-wins by timestamp — when hashes differ AND modification windows overlap (~10s), newer side wins per field; losers logged to `sprk_syncerror`. Integration tests cover round-trip echo + concurrent edit scenarios.
  </prompt>

  <role>Spaarke BFF API developer with distributed-sync expertise.</role>

  <goal>Three-layer loop prevention fully implemented and tested. Round-trip echo dropped. Concurrent edit (both sides within 10s) results in newer-side-wins per field. Conflict losers logged.</goal>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="FR-23">Three layers: synchash + thread-local skip-flag + per-field LWW. All three must work together.</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-06">Audit-log conflict losers to `sprk_syncerror`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md §F">Test obligation: unit + integration tests.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/smart-todo-decoupling-r3/design.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Define synced-fields canonicalization: serialize the in-scope `sprk_todo` fields (sprk_name, sprk_notes, sprk_duedate, statecode/statuscode, sprk_priorityscore) to canonical JSON (sorted keys); SHA-256; truncate to 16 hex chars.</step>
    <step order="2">Hook synchash compute into `TodoGraphSyncHandler.SyncAsync`: before PATCH, compute hash from outgoing fields; write hash to `sprk_synchash` post-PATCH.</step>
    <step order="3">Implement thread-local skip-flag (`AsyncLocal&lt;bool&gt; SkipOutbound`) — webhook handler sets to `true` during the Dataverse update; the plugin checks and skips enqueue when set.</step>
    <step order="4">Implement per-field LWW resolution: on inbound notification, compare incoming hash with stored hash; if different AND timestamps within 10s window, resolve field-by-field by `modifiedOn`; log losers to `sprk_syncerror`.</step>
    <step order="5">Integration tests: (a) outbound write → inbound notification of own change → dropped by synchash; (b) concurrent edit both sides within 10s → newer-per-field wins, loser logged; (c) thread-local skip-flag isolates inbound writes from triggering outbound.</step>
    <step order="6">Run `dotnet build` + `dotnet test`. BFF publish-size + CVE checks.</step>
    <step order="7">Update TASK-INDEX.md status to ✅ completed.</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">Updates to `TodoGraphSyncHandler.cs` for synchash + skip-flag + LWW</output>
    <output type="test">`tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Todo/LoopPreventionTests.cs`</output>
    <output type="test">`tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/` (sync round-trip + concurrent-edit scenarios)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Round-trip echo (own write → own notification) is dropped.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Concurrent edit (both sides within 10s) resolves per-field LWW.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Conflict losers logged to `sprk_syncerror`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Thread-local skip-flag prevents inbound writes from triggering outbound.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Integration tests pass.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <protocol>FULL rigor. Step 9.5 runs adr-check + code-review. Integration tests required.</protocol>
  </execution>
</task>
